<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: 1 Feb 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hindustan Times 1 Feb 2004 [EDITED]
<http://www.hindustantimes.com/news/181_556544,0050.htm>

Bangladesh fever that killed 20 identified as encephalitis
----------------------------------------------------------
A mysterious disease which claimed 20 lives in Bangladesh has been proven
to be viral encephalitis and not the bird flu, a top official said on Sunday.
"There is no evidence of any one afflicted by bird flu disease in
Bangladesh," Sarwar Kamal, Secretary, Ministry of Health, told reporters in
Dhaka. A laboratory in the United States detected the Nipah virus which
caused the viral encephalitis, he said.
20 people, mostly children, died in the last 2 weeks in 3 districts of the
mysterious disease. The test results on samples taken from patients were
received from the US today, Kamal said.
But it still remained a mystery how is the disease spread and so far
attacked 66 people, he said adding a delegation from the World Health
Organization is expected here on 5 Feb 2004 to study the outbreak.
Meanwhile, poultry associations across the country are seeking to dispel
fears about bird flu, which was affecting the sale of their products.
--
